Route 53

Route 53 is a globally distributed DNS service that routes users to endpoints using routing policies, health checks, and low-latency name servers.”

Which routing policy would you use for blue-green deployment?

Answer: Failover Routing

Which routing policy would you use for Canary deployment?

Canary is Route 53 Weighted Routing — Split traffic by %, Example: 80% old version, 20% new"


🔸 Simple Routing  -- within region
One record → one resource

🔸 Weighted Routing               -----------  Canary deployment
Split traffic by %
👉 Example: 80% old version, 20% new

🔸 Latency-based Routing
Route to lowest latency region

🔸 Failover Routing                -----------   blue-green deployment
Primary + secondary (DR setup)

🔸 Geolocation Routing
Based on user location

For same routing policy we can create multiple record
